								<string>PromptForUserInput</string>
								<key>Prompt</key>
								<string>This macro provides a method to “paste” text into fields that are otherwise restricted (e.g., a password confirmation).

Optionally change settings below and then select the 𝗜𝗻𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘁 𝗧𝗲𝘅𝘁 button.

During the 𝗪𝗮𝗶𝘁, move the cursor to the target location. After the wait, the 𝗧𝗲𝘅𝘁 will be typed (or pasted) with an optional 𝗗𝗲𝗹𝗮𝘆 between typed (or pasted) characters.

👉🏿 𝗦𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗰𝗵 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗥𝗲𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗲, 𝗥𝗲𝗴𝗘𝘅 𝗣𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗻, 𝗪𝗮𝗶𝘁, 𝗠𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗼𝗱 and 𝗗𝗲𝗹𝗮𝘆 are saved for subsequent macro executions; 𝗧𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗜𝗻𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘁 always defaults to %𝗦𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗺𝗖𝗹𝗶𝗽𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱% but can be set to the %𝗧𝗿𝗶𝗴𝗴𝗲𝗿𝗖𝗹𝗶𝗽𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱% from a 𝗖𝗹𝗶𝗽𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱 𝗛𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗿𝘆 𝗦𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗲𝗿 or 𝗡𝗮𝗺𝗲𝗱 𝗖𝗹𝗶𝗽𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱 𝗦𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗲𝗿 𝘤𝘢𝘭𝘭𝘪𝘯𝘨 macro.

👉🏿 Default Settings: 𝗦𝗲𝗮𝗿𝗰𝗵 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗥𝗲𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗲 = %Variable%local_SearchAndReplace%; 𝗥𝗲𝗴𝗘𝘅 𝗣𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗻 = %Variable%local_RegExPattern%; 𝗪𝗮𝗶𝘁 = %Variable%local_Wait% 𝘴𝘦𝘤𝘰𝘯𝘥𝘴; 𝗠𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗼𝗱 = %Variable%local_Method%; 𝗗𝗲𝗹𝗮𝘆 = %Variable%local_Delay% 𝘩𝘶𝘯𝘥𝘳𝘦𝘥𝘵𝘩𝘴 𝘰𝘧 𝘴𝘦𝘤𝘰𝘯𝘥𝘴

👉🏿 𝗧𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗜𝗻𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘁 includes %Variable%local_LineCount% %Variable%local_LineLabel%, %Variable%local_CharCount% %Variable%local_CharLabel%.
